📖 Definition

Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) is the process of understanding, analyzing, and preparing a dataset before building a Machine Learning model. It helps identify missing values, outliers, data distributions, feature relationships, and data quality issues.

Simple Definition:
EDA is the first step in every Machine Learning project where we understand the data before training the model.

🎯 Why Do We Need EDA?
To understand the dataset.
To identify missing values and duplicates.
To detect outliers and incorrect data.
To analyze relationships between features.
To clean and prepare data for Machine Learning.
To improve model accuracy and reliability.
